h3cDot11Sa.name: h3cDot11Sa

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

h3cDot11Sa.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
h3cDot11Sa.description: This MIB module provides spectrum analysis information. The initial revision of this MIB module. The spectrum analysis module on APs is able to examine the radio frequency (RF) environment in which the Wi-Fi network is operating, identify interference and classify its sources. An analysis of the results can then be used to quickly isolate issues with packet transmission, channel quality, and traffic congestion caused by contention with other devices operating in the same band or channel.

h3cDot11SaCfgTable.name: h3cDot11SaCfgTable
h3cDot11SaCfgTable.description: This table is used to configure spectrum analysis.

h3cDot11SaCfgEntry.name: h3cDot11SaCfgEntry
h3cDot11SaCfgEntry.description: This entry contains the spectrum analysis configuration.

h3cDot11SaCfgRadioType.name: h3cDot11SaCfgRadioType
h3cDot11SaCfgRadioType.description: Represents the radio type of the configuration.

h3cDot11SaEnable.name: h3cDot11SaEnable
h3cDot11SaEnable.description: Represents whether spectrum analysis is enabled globally.

h3cDot11SaRptDevType.name: h3cDot11SaRptDevType
h3cDot11SaRptDevType.description: Represents which types of interference devices should be reported.

h3cDot11SaTrapDevEnable.name: h3cDot11SaTrapDevEnable
h3cDot11SaTrapDevEnable.description: Represents whether the interference device trap is enabled.

h3cDot11SaTrapDevType.name: h3cDot11SaTrapDevType
h3cDot11SaTrapDevType.description: Represents which types of interference device will send traps when the interference device trap is enabled.

h3cDot11SaTrapAQEnable.name: h3cDot11SaTrapAQEnable
h3cDot11SaTrapAQEnable.description: Represents whether the air quality trap is enabled.

h3cDot11SaTrapAQThreshold.name: h3cDot11SaTrapAQThreshold
h3cDot11SaTrapAQThreshold.description: Represents the air quality trap threshold. When the air quality is below this value, the air quality trap will be sent.

h3cDot11SaDrivenRRMEnable.name: h3cDot11SaDrivenRRMEnable
h3cDot11SaDrivenRRMEnable.description: Configure whether to trigger RRM to run when an access point detects a certain level of interference.

h3cDot11SaDrivenRRMSnt.name: h3cDot11SaDrivenRRMSnt
h3cDot11SaDrivenRRMSnt.description: Configure the threshold at which RRM will be triggered. When the interference level for the access point rises above the threshold level, RRM initiates a local dynamic channel assignment (DCA) run and changes the channel of the affected access point radio if possible to improve network performance. Low represents a decreased sensitivity to changes in the environment while high represents an increased sensitivity.

h3cDot11SaRtFFTDataTable.name: h3cDot11SaRtFFTDataTable
h3cDot11SaRtFFTDataTable.description: This table contains the real-time FFT data for spectrum analysis.

h3cDot11SaRtFFTDataEntry.name: h3cDot11SaRtFFTDataEntry
h3cDot11SaRtFFTDataEntry.description: This entry contains the real-time FFT data for spectrum analysis.
